{a_n}
a_n = 1 + \frac{1}{1 \cdot 3} + \frac {1}{1 \cdot 3 \cdot 5} + \frac {1}{1 \cdot 3 \cdot 5 \cdot 7} + ... + \frac{1}{1 \cdot 3 \cdot ... \cdot (2n-1)}.
{a_n}
a_n \geq a_{n+1} \Rightarrow \frac{1}{1 \cdot 3 \cdot ... \cdot (2n-1)} \geq \frac{1}{1 \cdot 3 \cdot ... \cdot (2n-1) \cdot 2(n+1)-1} \Rightarrow \frac{1}{1 \cdot 3 \cdot ... \cdot (2n-1)} \geq \frac{1}{1 \cdot 3 \cdot ... \cdot (2n-1) \cdot 2n+1}.
a_n
1 \geq \frac{1}{2n+1}
a_n
b_n=\frac1{1\cdot3\cdot\ldots\cdot(2n-1)}
n\ge 1
b_{n+1}\le\frac13b_n
a_n=\sum_{k=1}^nb_k\le\sum_{k=1}^n\left(\frac13\right)^k\;.
a_n
a_{n+1}
a_{n+1} \leq 1 + a_n/3
a_1 = 1 < 3/2
a_n < 3/2
a_{n+1} \leq 1 + a_n/3 < 1 + 1/2 = 3/2
3/2
